5
00:00:47,361 --> 00:00:50,762
NARRATOR:
Once upon a time
in a faraway land

6
00:00:50,797 --> 00:00:54,563
a young prince lived
in a shining castle.

7
00:00:54,634 --> 00:00:58,229
Although he had
everything his heart desired

8
00:00:58,271 --> 00:01:03,334
the prince was spoiled,
selfish and unkind.

9
00:01:03,377 --> 00:01:05,777
But then, one winter's night

10
00:01:05,812 --> 00:01:09,111
an old beggar woman
came to the castle

11
00:01:09,149 --> 00:01:11,743
and offered him a single rose

12
00:01:11,785 --> 00:01:15,516
in return for shelter
from the bitter cold.

13
00:01:15,622 --> 00:01:18,182
Repulsed by
her haggard appearance

14
00:01:18,225 --> 00:01:23,094
the prince sneered at the gift
and turned the old woman away

15
00:01:23,130 --> 00:01:27,260
but she warned him not to be
deceived by appearances

16
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:29,393
for beauty is found within

17
00:01:29,436 --> 00:01:31,996
and when he dismissed her again

18
00:01:32,038 --> 00:01:35,007
the old woman's ugliness
melted away

19
00:01:35,041 --> 00:01:37,771
to reveal
a beautiful enchantress.

20
00:01:37,811 --> 00:01:41,303
The prince tried to apologize,
but it was too late

21
00:01:41,381 --> 00:01:45,044
for she had seen that there was
no love in his heart

22
00:01:45,085 --> 00:01:47,781
and as punishment,
she transformed him

23
00:01:47,821 --> 00:01:49,413
into a hideous beast

24
00:01:49,456 --> 00:01:52,721
and placed a powerful spell
on the castle

25
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:54,693
and all who lived there.

26
00:01:54,728 --> 00:01:57,128
Ashamed of his monstrous form

27
00:01:57,164 --> 00:02:00,691
the Beast concealed himself
inside his castle

28
00:02:00,734 --> 00:02:03,794
with a magic mirror
as his only window

29
00:02:03,837 --> 00:02:05,498
to the outside world.

30
00:02:05,572 --> 00:02:10,669
The rose she had offered
was truly an enchanted rose

31
00:02:10,710 --> 00:02:14,441
which would bloom
until his 21st year.

32
00:02:14,481 --> 00:02:17,314
lf he could learn
to love another

33
00:02:17,350 --> 00:02:22,515
and earn her love in return
by the time the last petal fell

34
00:02:22,589 --> 00:02:25,615
then the spell would be broken.

35
00:02:25,659 --> 00:02:31,097
lf not, he would be doomed
to remain a beast for all time.

36
00:02:31,131 --> 00:02:33,065
( thunder crashing )

37
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:37,331
As the years passed,
he fell into despair

38
00:02:37,370 --> 00:02:40,430
and lost all hope

39
00:02:40,474 --> 00:02:44,706
for who could ever learn
to love a beast?

40
00:02:52,052 --> 00:02:54,247
( rooster crowing )

41
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:59,284
( birds twittering )

42
