* Little town,
it's a quiet village *

43
00:03:16,943 --> 00:03:21,710
* Every day
like the one before *

44
00:03:21,748 --> 00:03:26,208
* Little town,
full of little people *

45
00:03:26,253 --> 00:03:31,850
* Waking up... to... say... *

46
00:03:31,892 --> 00:03:32,756
Bonjour!

47
00:03:32,792 --> 00:03:33,656
Bonjour!

48
00:03:33,693 --> 00:03:34,660
- Bonjour!
- Bonjour!

49
00:03:34,694 --> 00:03:35,285
Bonjour!

50
00:03:35,328 --> 00:03:36,955
* There goes the baker *

51
00:03:36,997 --> 00:03:39,864
* With his tray like always *

52
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:43,097
* The same old bread
and rolls to sell *

53
00:03:43,136 --> 00:03:44,967
* Every morning just the same *

54
00:03:45,005 --> 00:03:46,529
* Since the morning
that we came *

55
00:03:46,606 --> 00:03:48,267
* To this poor
provincial town... *

56
00:03:48,308 --> 00:03:49,297
Good morning, Belle.

57
00:03:49,342 --> 00:03:50,309
Good morning, Monsieur.

58
00:03:50,343 --> 00:03:51,310
Where are you off to?

59
00:03:51,378 --> 00:03:52,310
The bookshop.

60
00:03:52,345 --> 00:03:54,540
l just finished
the most wonderful story

61
00:03:54,648 --> 00:03:56,479
about a beanstalk
and an ogre, and...

62
00:03:56,516 --> 00:03:57,642
That's nice.

63
00:03:57,684 --> 00:03:58,946
Marie! The baguettes.

64
00:03:58,985 --> 00:04:00,509
Hurry up!

65
00:04:00,554 --> 00:04:01,521
* Look, there she goes *

66
00:04:01,555 --> 00:04:04,023
* The girl is strange,
no question *

67
00:04:04,057 --> 00:04:07,493
* Dazed and distracted,
can't you tell? *

68
00:04:07,561 --> 00:04:09,290
* Never part of any crowd *

69
00:04:09,329 --> 00:04:11,194
* 'Cause her head's
up on some cloud *

70
00:04:11,231 --> 00:04:15,167
* No denying she's a funny girl,
that Belle *

71
00:04:15,201 --> 00:04:16,361
* Bonjour *

72
00:04:16,403 --> 00:04:17,370
* Good day *

73
00:04:17,404 --> 00:04:19,133
* How is your family? *

74
00:04:19,172 --> 00:04:20,139
* Bonjour *

75
00:04:20,173 --> 00:04:21,162
* Good day *

76
00:04:21,207 --> 00:04:23,072
* How is your wife? *

77
00:04:23,143 --> 00:04:24,940
* l need six eggs *

78
00:04:24,978 --> 00:04:26,445
* That's too expensive *

79
00:04:26,479 --> 00:04:30,745
* There must be more
than this provincial life... *

80
00:04:30,784 --> 00:04:32,274
-MAN:
Ah, Belle.
( bell jingles )

81
00:04:32,319 --> 00:04:33,286
Good morning.

82
00:04:33,353 --> 00:04:35,184
l've come to return
the book l borrowed.

83
00:04:35,221 --> 00:04:36,188
Finished already?

84
00:04:36,222 --> 00:04:37,416
Oh, l couldn't put it down.

85
00:04:37,457 --> 00:04:38,481
Have you got anything new?

86
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:39,523
( chuckling )

87
00:04:39,626 --> 00:04:40,684
Not since yesterday.

88
00:04:40,727 --> 00:04:42,092
That's all right.

89
00:04:42,128 --> 00:04:44,153
l'll borrow... this one.

90
00:04:44,197 --> 00:04:45,255
That one?

91
00:04:45,298 --> 00:04:46,697
But you've read it twice.

92
00:04:46,733 --> 00:04:48,963
Well, it's my favorite--
far-off places

93
00:04:49,002 --> 00:04:50,367
daring sword fights

94
00:04:50,403 --> 00:04:52,234
magic spells, a
prince in disguise.

95
00:04:52,272 --> 00:04:55,469
lf you like it
all that much, it's yours.

96
00:04:55,508 --> 00:04:57,499
-But, sir...
-l insist.

97
00:04:57,611 --> 00:04:58,543
Well, thank you.

98
00:04:58,645 --> 00:04:59,839
Thank you very much.

99
00:04:59,879 --> 00:05:01,403
* Look, there she goes *

100
00:05:01,481 --> 00:05:04,041
* That girl is so peculiar *

101
00:05:04,084 --> 00:05:07,383
* l wonder
if she's feeling well *

102
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:09,183
* With a dreamy, far-off look *

103
00:05:09,222 --> 00:05:10,951
* And her nose stuck in a book *

104
00:05:10,991 --> 00:05:15,087
* What a puzzle to the rest
of us is Belle *

105
00:05:15,128 --> 00:05:20,998
* Oh, isn't this amazing? *

106
00:05:21,034 --> 00:05:30,466
* lt's my favorite part
because you'll see *

107
00:05:30,610 --> 00:05:36,708
* Here's where she meets
Prince Charming *

108
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:40,481
* But she won't discover
that it's him *

109
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:43,921
* Till Chapter Three *

110
00:05:43,957 --> 00:05:45,948
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

111
00:05:45,992 --> 00:05:49,484
* Now, it's no wonder
that her name means beauty *

112
00:05:49,596 --> 00:05:52,759
* Her looks have got
no parallel *

113
00:05:52,799 --> 00:05:54,664
* But behind
that fair facade *

114
00:05:54,701 --> 00:05:56,794
* l'm afraid
she's rather odd *

115
00:05:56,836 --> 00:05:58,770
* Very different
from the rest of us *

116
00:05:58,805 --> 00:06:00,636
GROUP:
* She's nothing like
the rest of us *

117
00:06:00,674 --> 00:06:04,474
* Yes, different
from the rest of us is Belle *

118
00:06:04,544 --> 00:06:06,478
( gun fires )

119
00:06:06,513 --> 00:06:09,277
( panting )

120
00:06:09,315 --> 00:06:11,306
Wow, you didn't miss
a shot, Gaston.

121
00:06:11,351 --> 00:06:12,409
You're the greatest hunter

122
00:06:12,452 --> 00:06:13,646
in the whole world.

123
00:06:13,687 --> 00:06:15,314
l know.

124
00:06:15,355 --> 00:06:17,323
No beast alive
stands a chance against you

125
00:06:17,357 --> 00:06:19,291
and no girl,
for that matter.

126
00:06:19,325 --> 00:06:20,292
lt's true, Lefou

127
00:06:20,326 --> 00:06:22,726
and l've got my sights set
on that one.

128
00:06:22,762 --> 00:06:24,491
LEFOU:
The inventor's daughter?

129
00:06:24,597 --> 00:06:27,327
She's the one-- the lucky girl
l'm going to marry.

130
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:28,425
But, she...

131
00:06:28,468 --> 00:06:29,765
The most beautiful girl in town.

132
00:06:29,803 --> 00:06:30,929
l know, but...

133
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:32,733
That makes her the best

134
00:06:32,806 --> 00:06:34,433
and don't l
deserve the best?

135
00:06:34,507 --> 00:06:35,496
Well, of course.

136
00:06:35,608 --> 00:06:36,768
l mean, you do, but...

137
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:40,041
* Right from the moment
when l met her, saw her *

138
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:40,180
* l said, ''She's gorgeous,''
and l fell *

139
00:06:40,180 --> 00:06:43,980
* l said, ''She's gorgeous,''
and l fell *

140
00:06:44,017 --> 00:06:47,976
* Here in town there's only she
who is beautiful as me *

141
00:06:48,054 --> 00:06:52,047
* So, l'm making plans
to woo and marry Belle *

142
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:56,061
* Look, there he goes,
isn't he dreamy? *

143
00:06:56,096 --> 00:06:59,156
* Monsieur Gaston,
oh, he's so cute *

144
00:06:59,232 --> 00:07:02,861
* Be still, my heart,
l'm hardly breathing *

145
00:07:02,902 --> 00:07:06,360
* He's such a tall, dark,
strong and handsome brute *

146
00:07:06,439 --> 00:07:08,669
-* Bonjour * * Pardon *
-* Good day * * Mais oui *

147
00:07:08,742 --> 00:07:10,642
-* You call this bacon? *
-* What lovely grapes *

148
00:07:10,677 --> 00:07:12,269
-* Ten yards * * Some cheese *
-* 'Scuse me * * One pound *

149
00:07:12,345 --> 00:07:13,312
* l'll get the knife *

150
00:07:13,346 --> 00:07:14,313
* Please let me through *

151
00:07:14,380 --> 00:07:15,404
* This bread * * Those fish *

152
00:07:15,448 --> 00:07:16,437
* lt's stale * * They smell *

153
00:07:16,483 --> 00:07:17,507
* Madame's mistaken *

154
00:07:17,550 --> 00:07:18,812
* There must be more *

155
00:07:18,852 --> 00:07:21,421
* Than this provincial life *

156
00:07:21,421 --> 00:07:25,152
* Just watch, l'm going
to make Belle my wife *

157
00:07:25,191 --> 00:07:26,158
* Look, there she goes *

158
00:07:26,192 --> 00:07:28,854
* A girl who's strange
but special *

159
00:07:28,928 --> 00:07:32,193
* A most peculiar mademoiselle *

160
00:07:32,232 --> 00:07:33,756
* lt's a pity and a sin *

161
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,562
* She doesn't quite fit in *

162
00:07:35,668 --> 00:07:37,363
* 'Cause she really is
a funny girl *

163
00:07:37,403 --> 00:07:39,701
* A beauty but a funny girl *

164
00:07:39,773 --> 00:07:44,733
* She really is a funny girl *

165
00:07:44,811 --> 00:07:47,905
* That Belle... *

166
00:07:47,981 --> 00:07:50,882
GASTON:
* Bonjour, bonjour. *

167
00:07:50,917 --> 00:07:54,120
( song ends )

168
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,348
Hello, Belle.

169
00:07:55,388 --> 00:07:57,083
Bonjour, Gaston.

170
00:07:57,123 --> 00:07:59,250
Gaston,
may l have my book, please?

171
00:07:59,292 --> 00:08:00,418
How can you read this?

172
00:08:00,460 --> 00:08:01,552
There's no pictures.

173
00:08:01,594 --> 00:08:03,653
Well, some people
use their imagination.

174
00:08:03,696 --> 00:08:05,755
Belle, it's about time
you got your head

175
00:08:05,832 --> 00:08:06,799
out of those books

176
00:08:06,866 --> 00:08:09,562
and paid attention
to more important things...

177
00:08:09,636 --> 00:08:10,728
like me.

178
00:08:10,804 --> 00:08:12,567
( gasping and sighing )

179
00:08:12,672 --> 00:08:15,106
The whole town's
talking about it.

180
00:08:15,141 --> 00:08:17,166
lt's not right
for a woman to read.

181
00:08:17,210 --> 00:08:19,974
Soon she starts getting ideas,
and thinking...

182
00:08:20,046 --> 00:08:21,536
Gaston,
you are positively primeval.

183
00:08:21,581 --> 00:08:23,173
( chuckling ):
Why, thank you, Belle.

184
00:08:23,216 --> 00:08:24,478
What do you say you and me

185
00:08:24,517 --> 00:08:25,984
take a walk over to the tavern

186
00:08:26,052 --> 00:08:27,576
and take a look
at my trophies?

187
00:08:27,620 --> 00:08:29,383
Maybe some other time.

188
00:08:29,422 --> 00:08:30,548
What's wrong with her?

189
00:08:30,590 --> 00:08:31,579
She's crazy.

190
00:08:31,624 --> 00:08:33,148
He's gorgeous.

191
00:08:33,193 --> 00:08:34,524
Please, Gaston, l can't.

192
00:08:34,561 --> 00:08:36,791
l have to get home
to help my father.

193
00:08:36,863 --> 00:08:37,830
Good-bye.

194
00:08:37,864 --> 00:08:39,331
( laughing ):
That crazy old loon--

195
00:08:39,365 --> 00:08:40,832
he needs all the
help he can get.

196
00:08:40,867 --> 00:08:41,834
( laughing )

197
00:08:41,868 --> 00:08:43,495
Don't talk about my father

198
00:08:43,536 --> 00:08:44,434
that way.

199
00:08:44,504 --> 00:08:47,166
Yeah, don't talk
about her father that way.

200
00:08:47,207 --> 00:08:48,902
My father is not crazy.

201
00:08:48,975 --> 00:08:49,964
He's a genius.

202
00:08:50,009 --> 00:08:51,943
( explosion and whistling )

203
00:08:52,011 --> 00:08:53,410
( both laughing )

204
00:08:53,446 --> 00:08:54,708
Ooh!

205
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:59,384
( man coughing )

206
00:09:02,956 --> 00:09:04,685
( coughing ):
Papa?

207
00:09:04,724 --> 00:09:07,192
How on earth did that happen?

208
00:09:07,227 --> 00:09:08,694
Doggone it!

209
00:09:08,728 --> 00:09:10,559
Are you all right, Papa?

210
00:09:10,597 --> 00:09:14,363
l'm about ready to give
up on this hunk of junk.

211
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,197
You always say that.

212
00:09:16,236 --> 00:09:17,396
l mean it this time.

213
00:09:17,437 --> 00:09:18,369
l'll never get

214
00:09:18,404 --> 00:09:20,736
this boneheaded contraption
to work!

215
00:09:20,773 --> 00:09:21,899
Yes, you will

216
00:09:21,975 --> 00:09:24,273
and you'll win first prize
at the fair tomorrow.

217
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:25,242
Humph!

218
00:09:25,278 --> 00:09:28,213
And become
a world-famous inventor.

219
00:09:28,248 --> 00:09:30,216
You really believe that?

220
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,774
l always have.

221
00:09:31,818 --> 00:09:33,911
Well, what are we waiting for?

222
00:09:33,987 --> 00:09:36,581
l'll have this thing fixed
in no time.

223
00:09:36,623 --> 00:09:38,022
Hand me that, uh...

224
00:09:38,057 --> 00:09:39,752
dog-legged clincher, there.

225
00:09:39,792 --> 00:09:42,590
So, did you have a
good time in town today?

226
00:09:42,695 --> 00:09:44,754
l got a new book.

227
00:09:44,797 --> 00:09:48,233
Papa, do you think l'm odd?

228
00:09:48,301 --> 00:09:49,529
My daughter? Odd?

229
00:09:49,569 --> 00:09:52,470
Where would you get
an idea like that?

230
00:09:52,505 --> 00:09:53,597
Oh, l don't know.

231
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,507
lt's just that l'm not sure
l fit in here.

232
00:09:56,542 --> 00:09:58,976
There's no one
l can really talk to.

233
00:09:59,012 --> 00:10:00,775
What about that Gaston?

234
00:10:00,813 --> 00:10:02,542
He's a handsome fellow.

235
00:10:02,582 --> 00:10:06,416
He's handsome, all right,
and rude, and conceited, and...

236
00:10:06,452 --> 00:10:08,147
Oh, Papa, he's not for me.

237
00:10:08,187 --> 00:10:09,586
Well, don't you worry

238
00:10:09,622 --> 00:10:12,557
'cause this invention's
going to be the start

239
00:10:12,592 --> 00:10:14,025
of a new life for us.

240
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:15,618
l think that's done it.

241
00:10:15,662 --> 00:10:17,527
Now, let's give it a try.

242
00:10:17,563 --> 00:10:19,292
( whistle blowing )

243
00:10:19,332 --> 00:10:20,594
( steam hissing )

244
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:22,931
( gears clanking )

245
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:27,237
( whirring )

246
00:10:31,678 --> 00:10:33,043
lt works!

247
00:10:33,079 --> 00:10:35,377
lt does?

248
00:10:35,415 --> 00:10:36,575
( glass breaking )
-lt does!

249
00:10:36,616 --> 00:10:37,583
You did it!

250
00:10:37,617 --> 00:10:38,879
You really did it!

251
00:10:38,918 --> 00:10:40,647
Hitch up Philippe, girl.

252
00:10:40,687 --> 00:10:42,951
l'm off to the fair!

253
00:10:42,989 --> 00:10:44,422
( grunting )

254
00:10:44,457 --> 00:10:45,685
Good-bye, Papa.

255
00:10:45,758 --> 00:10:47,123
Good luck.

256
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:50,288
Good-bye, Belle,
and take care while l'm gone.

257
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,069
( nickers anxiously )

258
00:11:08,114 --> 00:11:09,138
We should be there
by now.

259
00:11:09,182 --> 00:11:10,240
( hooting )

260
00:11:10,283 --> 00:11:12,444
Maybe we've missed
the turn.

261
00:11:12,485 --> 00:11:14,385
l guess l should have taken...

262
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:15,853
Wait a minute.

263
00:11:18,558 --> 00:11:19,957
( nickering )

264
00:11:19,993 --> 00:11:22,291
Let's go this way.

265
00:11:22,328 --> 00:11:24,296
( nickering )

266
00:11:24,330 --> 00:11:26,890
( distant roaring )

267
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:28,662
( birds chirping )

