( growling )

301
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:02,828
( grunting )

302
00:13:03,830 --> 00:13:05,354
( thunder crashing )

303
00:13:05,398 --> 00:13:07,195
( menacing growl )

304
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:09,201
Help!

305
00:13:09,235 --> 00:13:11,604
ls someone there?!

306
00:13:11,604 --> 00:13:13,128
Help!

307
00:13:13,172 --> 00:13:14,730
( growling )

308
00:13:17,443 --> 00:13:20,213
Oh!

309
00:13:20,213 --> 00:13:21,202
( crying out )

310
00:13:21,247 --> 00:13:22,771
( wolves snarling )

311
00:13:24,784 --> 00:13:25,751
( gasps )

312
00:13:30,990 --> 00:13:32,457
( thunder crashing )

313
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:39,098
( creaking )

314
00:13:39,132 --> 00:13:41,566
What...?

315
00:13:41,601 --> 00:13:44,593
Oh...

316
00:13:44,637 --> 00:13:45,934
( creaking )

317
00:13:48,274 --> 00:13:50,333
( voice echoing ):
Hello?

318
00:13:52,411 --> 00:13:53,935
Hello?

319
00:13:54,013 --> 00:13:57,312
MALE 1 :
Poor fellow, must have
lost his way in the woods.

320
00:13:57,350 --> 00:13:59,648
MALE 2:
Keep quiet; maybe
he'll go away.

321
00:13:59,685 --> 00:14:01,949
ls someone there?

322
00:14:01,988 --> 00:14:05,685
Not a word, Lumiere;
not one word.

323
00:14:05,791 --> 00:14:09,693
l don't mean to intrude,
but l've lost my horse

324
00:14:09,729 --> 00:14:11,924
and l need a place to stay

325
00:14:11,964 --> 00:14:13,022
for the night.

326
00:14:13,099 --> 00:14:15,067
Oh, Cogsworth, have a heart.

327
00:14:15,134 --> 00:14:16,692
Shh!

328
00:14:16,802 --> 00:14:17,700
( sizzling )

329
00:14:17,803 --> 00:14:18,770
( yelping )

330
00:14:18,838 --> 00:14:21,500
Of course, Monsieur,
you are welcome here.

331
00:14:21,541 --> 00:14:23,065
Who said that?

332
00:14:23,142 --> 00:14:25,110
Over here.

333
00:14:25,144 --> 00:14:26,406
Where?

334
00:14:26,445 --> 00:14:27,343
Allo.

335
00:14:27,380 --> 00:14:27,846
( gasps )

336
00:14:27,914 --> 00:14:28,812
( grunts )

337
00:14:28,848 --> 00:14:30,713
( groans )

338
00:14:30,816 --> 00:14:32,545
lncredible.

339
00:14:32,585 --> 00:14:35,281
Well, now you've done it,
Lumiere.

340
00:14:35,321 --> 00:14:37,380
Splendid, just peachy. Ah!

341
00:14:37,423 --> 00:14:38,856
How is this accomplished?

342
00:14:38,891 --> 00:14:40,051
Put me down at once!

343
00:14:40,126 --> 00:14:41,093
Stop that!

344
00:14:41,127 --> 00:14:42,116
( giggling )

345
00:14:42,195 --> 00:14:43,496
Stop that, l say.

346
00:14:43,496 --> 00:14:45,464
( chuckling )

347
00:14:45,498 --> 00:14:46,465
Ow!

348
00:14:46,499 --> 00:14:47,557
( yelling )

349
00:14:48,901 --> 00:14:51,597
Huh... Close that at once.

350
00:14:51,637 --> 00:14:53,104
Do you mind?!

351
00:14:53,139 --> 00:14:54,504
l-l beg your pardon.

352
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:57,475
lt's, it's just
that l've never seen a...

353
00:14:57,510 --> 00:15:00,877
( snorting )

354
00:15:00,913 --> 00:15:03,040
( sneezing )

355
00:15:03,115 --> 00:15:04,878
( squeaking )

356
00:15:04,917 --> 00:15:06,509
( sniffling )

357
00:15:06,552 --> 00:15:08,679
Oh, you are soaked to the bone,
Monsieur.

358
00:15:08,788 --> 00:15:10,847
Come, warm yourself by the fire.

359
00:15:10,923 --> 00:15:11,890
Thank you.

360
00:15:11,924 --> 00:15:13,152
COGSWORTH:
No, no, no.

361
00:15:13,226 --> 00:15:16,525
You know what the master will do
if he finds him here.

362
00:15:16,562 --> 00:15:20,328
l demand
that you stop right there.

363
00:15:20,366 --> 00:15:21,567
Oh, no, no!

364
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:23,535
Not the master's chair.

365
00:15:23,569 --> 00:15:25,127
( barking )

366
00:15:25,204 --> 00:15:26,364
l'm not seeing this!

367
00:15:26,405 --> 00:15:27,633
l am not seeing this!

368
00:15:27,673 --> 00:15:32,235
( chuckling ):
Well, hello there, boy.

369
00:15:32,278 --> 00:15:34,371
( friendly panting )

370
00:15:36,482 --> 00:15:37,676
What service.

371
00:15:37,717 --> 00:15:40,481
All right,
this has gone far enough.

372
00:15:40,519 --> 00:15:42,009
l'm in charge here.

373
00:15:42,088 --> 00:15:44,386
How would you like
a nice spot of tea, sir?

374
00:15:44,423 --> 00:15:45,981
lt'll warm you up
in no time.

375
00:15:46,058 --> 00:15:48,026
No. No tea.

376
00:15:48,060 --> 00:15:49,357
No tea!

377
00:15:50,896 --> 00:15:52,056
( giggling )

378
00:15:52,131 --> 00:15:53,621
His mustache tickles, Mama.

379
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:54,633
Oh!

380
00:15:54,667 --> 00:15:55,895
( chuckling )

381
00:15:55,935 --> 00:15:57,061
Hello.

382
00:15:57,136 --> 00:15:59,161
( ominous rumbling )

383
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:02,107
( clattering )

384
00:16:02,141 --> 00:16:03,802
Uh-oh.

385
00:16:03,843 --> 00:16:05,868
Oh...

386
00:16:08,247 --> 00:16:11,683
( growling deeply )

387
00:16:11,751 --> 00:16:12,581
Ah...

388
00:16:12,618 --> 00:16:14,586
There's a stranger here.

389
00:16:14,620 --> 00:16:16,110
Master, allow me to explain.

390
00:16:16,188 --> 00:16:18,179
The gentleman
was lost in the woods.

391
00:16:18,257 --> 00:16:19,485
He was cold and wet...

392
00:16:19,525 --> 00:16:21,390
( roaring thunderously )

393
00:16:21,427 --> 00:16:23,895
Master, l'd like
to take this moment to say

394
00:16:23,929 --> 00:16:25,863
l was against this
from the start.

395
00:16:25,898 --> 00:16:27,092
lt was all his fault.

396
00:16:27,166 --> 00:16:30,294
l tried to stop them,
but would they listen to me? No.

397
00:16:30,336 --> 00:16:32,566
( roaring
thunderously )

398
00:16:35,308 --> 00:16:36,332
( gasping )

399
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:37,399
Who are you?

400
00:16:37,443 --> 00:16:38,671
What are you doing here?

401
00:16:38,711 --> 00:16:41,179
l-l-l was lost in the woods,
and, and...

402
00:16:41,213 --> 00:16:42,145
You're not welcome here!

403
00:16:42,181 --> 00:16:45,241
l-l-l'm sorry.

404
00:16:45,318 --> 00:16:46,444
What are you staring at?!

405
00:16:46,485 --> 00:16:47,509
N-Nothing.

406
00:16:47,553 --> 00:16:49,817
So, you've come to stare

407
00:16:49,855 --> 00:16:51,220
at the Beast, have you?!

408
00:16:51,290 --> 00:16:52,587
Please, l meant no harm!

409
00:16:52,625 --> 00:16:54,490
l just needed
a place to stay.

410
00:16:54,527 --> 00:16:56,427
l'll give you
a place to stay.

411
00:16:56,462 --> 00:16:57,588
Oh, no...!

412
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:58,927
Please! Oh, no!

413
00:16:58,964 --> 00:17:01,398
( door slams
with an echoing thud )

414
00:17:04,737 --> 00:17:07,501
Oh, boy, Belle's going to get
the surprise of her life

415
00:17:07,540 --> 00:17:08,905
huh, Gaston?

416
00:17:08,941 --> 00:17:11,569
Yep. This is her lucky day.

417
00:17:11,610 --> 00:17:13,578
( thudding )

418
00:17:13,612 --> 00:17:14,909
( Gaston clears throat )

419
00:17:14,947 --> 00:17:18,007
l'd like to thank you all
for coming to my wedding.

420
00:17:18,084 --> 00:17:20,712
But first l'd better go in there
and propose to the girl.

421
00:17:20,753 --> 00:17:22,721
( laughing )

422
00:17:22,788 --> 00:17:23,720
( sobbing )

423
00:17:23,789 --> 00:17:25,381
And you, Lefou--
now, when

424
00:17:25,424 --> 00:17:26,948
Belle and l come
out that door...

425
00:17:27,026 --> 00:17:27,958
Oh, l know, l know!

426
00:17:27,993 --> 00:17:29,426
l-l strike up the band.

427
00:17:29,462 --> 00:17:32,829
( playing ''Here Comes the Bride''
at fast tempo )

428
00:17:32,865 --> 00:17:33,957
Not yet!

429
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:35,728
Sorry.

430
00:17:35,801 --> 00:17:37,769
( knocking )

431
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:46,978
( groans )

432
00:17:47,012 --> 00:17:48,274
Gaston.

433
00:17:48,347 --> 00:17:50,076
What a pleasant surprise.

434
00:17:50,149 --> 00:17:51,411
lsn't it, though?

435
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:53,577
l'm just full of surprises.

436
00:17:53,619 --> 00:17:55,746
You know, Belle, there's
not a girl in town

437
00:17:55,788 --> 00:17:57,756
who wouldn't love
to be in your shoes.

438
00:17:57,790 --> 00:17:59,917
This is the day...

439
00:17:59,992 --> 00:18:01,482
Hmm.

440
00:18:01,527 --> 00:18:02,721
Yeah.

441
00:18:02,762 --> 00:18:03,696
This is the day your
dreams come true.

442
00:18:03,696 --> 00:18:04,924
This is the day your
dreams come true.

443
00:18:04,997 --> 00:18:08,262
What do you know
about my dreams, Gaston?

444
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:11,792
Plenty. Here, picture this:

445
00:18:11,871 --> 00:18:13,896
A rustic hunting lodge

446
00:18:13,973 --> 00:18:17,033
my latest kill
roasting on the fire

447
00:18:17,109 --> 00:18:20,169
and my little wife,
massaging my feet

448
00:18:20,212 --> 00:18:21,611
while the little ones

449
00:18:21,647 --> 00:18:23,308
play on the floor
with the dogs.

450
00:18:23,349 --> 00:18:24,543
We'll have six or seven.

451
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:25,447
Dogs?

452
00:18:25,484 --> 00:18:26,451
No, Belle!

453
00:18:26,485 --> 00:18:27,679
Strapping boys,
like me.

454
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,687
lmagine that.

455
00:18:28,721 --> 00:18:29,688
And do you know

456
00:18:29,722 --> 00:18:31,246
who that little
wife will be?

457
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:32,257
Let me think.

458
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:33,315
You, Belle.

459
00:18:33,359 --> 00:18:34,519
Gaston, l'm...

460
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:35,857
l'm...

461
00:18:35,895 --> 00:18:37,157
speechless.

462
00:18:37,196 --> 00:18:39,687
l really don't
know what to say.

463
00:18:39,765 --> 00:18:40,732
Say you'll marry me.

464
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:43,894
l'm very sorry,
Gaston, but...

465
00:18:43,969 --> 00:18:44,936
but...

466
00:18:44,970 --> 00:18:46,232
l just don't deserve you.

467
00:18:46,272 --> 00:18:48,103
-Whoa!
-( water splashes )

468
00:18:48,174 --> 00:18:51,871
( playing
''Here Comes the Bride'' )

469
00:18:58,684 --> 00:18:59,912
( pig oinks )

470
00:18:59,985 --> 00:19:01,179
( squeals )

471
00:19:01,220 --> 00:19:03,222
So, how'd it go?

472
00:19:03,222 --> 00:19:04,655
( grunts )

473
00:19:04,690 --> 00:19:08,023
l'll have Belle for my wife.

474
00:19:08,060 --> 00:19:10,824
Make no mistake about that!

475
00:19:10,863 --> 00:19:12,831
Touchy.

476
00:19:12,865 --> 00:19:13,923
( snorting )

477
00:19:19,905 --> 00:19:22,635
ls he gone?

478
00:19:22,675 --> 00:19:23,835
( chickens clucking )

479
00:19:23,876 --> 00:19:25,173
Can you imagine?

480
00:19:25,244 --> 00:19:27,075
He asked me to marry him.

481
00:19:27,146 --> 00:19:30,638
Me, the wife of that boorish,
brainless...

482
00:19:30,683 --> 00:19:33,379
* Madame Gaston *

483
00:19:33,419 --> 00:19:35,046
* Can't you just see it? *

484
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:36,553
* Madame Gaston *

485
00:19:36,589 --> 00:19:37,920
* His little wife *

486
00:19:37,957 --> 00:19:39,083
( clucking, bleating )

487
00:19:39,158 --> 00:19:41,718
* No, sir, not me *

488
00:19:41,827 --> 00:19:43,089
* l guarantee it *

489
00:19:43,162 --> 00:19:46,723
* l want much more
than this provincial life *

490
00:19:55,908 --> 00:20:00,868
* l want adventure
in the great, wide somewhere *

491
00:20:00,946 --> 00:20:04,609
* l want it more
than l can tell *

492
00:20:04,650 --> 00:20:09,417
* And for once
it might be grand *

493
00:20:09,455 --> 00:20:12,913
* To have someone understand *

494
00:20:12,992 --> 00:20:19,625
* l want so much more
than they've got planned. *

495
00:20:19,665 --> 00:20:23,536
( horse neighs )

496
00:20:23,536 --> 00:20:24,764
Philippe!
What are you doing here?

497
00:20:24,803 --> 00:20:26,236
Where's...?

498
00:20:26,272 --> 00:20:27,364
Where's Papa?

499
00:20:27,439 --> 00:20:28,770
Where is he, Philippe?

500
00:20:28,841 --> 00:20:30,035
What happened?

501
00:20:30,075 --> 00:20:31,440
Oh, we have to find him.

502
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:34,343
You have to take me to him.

503
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:37,349
( ominous music playing )

504
00:20:46,792 --> 00:20:48,225
What is this place?

505
00:20:48,260 --> 00:20:49,591
( snorting )

506
00:20:49,628 --> 00:20:50,652
( neighing )

507
00:20:50,696 --> 00:20:51,663
Philippe, please!

508
00:20:51,697 --> 00:20:52,721
Steady!

509
00:20:52,765 --> 00:20:54,323
( neighing continues )

510
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,697
Steady.

511
00:20:55,734 --> 00:20:58,726
( gasps )

512
00:20:58,771 --> 00:21:01,035
Papa.

513
00:21:01,073 --> 00:21:03,974
Couldn't keep quiet, could we?

514
00:21:04,009 --> 00:21:06,307
Just had to invite him
to stay, didn't we?

515
00:21:06,345 --> 00:21:07,869
Serve him tea.

516
00:21:07,913 --> 00:21:09,437
Sit in the master's chair.

517
00:21:09,515 --> 00:21:10,880
Pet the pooch.

518
00:21:10,916 --> 00:21:12,884
l was trying
to be hospitable.

519
00:21:12,918 --> 00:21:13,850
( door creaking )

520
00:21:13,886 --> 00:21:15,444
( echoing ):
Hello?

521
00:21:15,521 --> 00:21:18,354
ls anyone here?

522
00:21:18,390 --> 00:21:22,121
Hello? Papa?

523
00:21:22,161 --> 00:21:24,254
Papa?

524
00:21:24,330 --> 00:21:26,423
Are you here?

525
00:21:26,498 --> 00:21:29,467
Mama, there's a girl
in the castle.

526
00:21:29,501 --> 00:21:32,868
Now, Chip, l'll not have you
making up such wild stories.

527
00:21:32,905 --> 00:21:34,372
Really, Mama.
l saw her.

528
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:35,372
Not another word.

529
00:21:35,407 --> 00:21:36,374
But...

530
00:21:36,408 --> 00:21:37,375
lnto the tub.

531
00:21:37,409 --> 00:21:38,376
Woop...

532
00:21:38,410 --> 00:21:40,378
Well! l saw a girl
in the castle!

533
00:21:40,412 --> 00:21:42,972
See? l told you.

534
00:21:43,015 --> 00:21:44,983
lrresponsible,
devil-may-care

535
00:21:45,017 --> 00:21:46,951
waxy-eared,
slack-jawed...

536
00:21:46,986 --> 00:21:48,146
BELLE:
Papa?

537
00:21:49,922 --> 00:21:50,854
Did you see that?

538
00:21:52,324 --> 00:21:53,348
( gasps )

539
00:21:53,425 --> 00:21:54,790
lt's a girl!

540
00:21:54,860 --> 00:21:56,122
l know it's a girl.

541
00:21:56,161 --> 00:21:57,059
Don't you see?

542
00:21:57,096 --> 00:21:58,256
She's the one--

543
00:21:58,297 --> 00:21:59,958
the girl we have
been waiting for.

544
00:21:59,999 --> 00:22:01,398
She has come
to break the spell!

545
00:22:01,433 --> 00:22:02,764
Wait a minute!
Wait a minute!

546
00:22:06,472 --> 00:22:07,939
Papa?

547
00:22:07,973 --> 00:22:09,235
( door creaks )

548
00:22:09,274 --> 00:22:10,605
Papa?

549
00:22:12,478 --> 00:22:13,672
Hello?

550
00:22:13,712 --> 00:22:15,646
