00:32:38,069 --> 00:32:40,697
Oh, but you must.

826
00:32:40,739 --> 00:32:43,105
( sputtering )

827
00:32:43,141 --> 00:32:46,008
Dinner is served.

828
00:32:46,044 --> 00:32:48,103
( snarling )

829
00:32:48,146 --> 00:32:49,841
What's taking so long?

830
00:32:49,881 --> 00:32:51,746
l told her to come down.

831
00:32:51,783 --> 00:32:53,080
Why isn't she here yet?

832
00:32:53,118 --> 00:32:54,847
Oh, try to be
patient, sir.

833
00:32:54,886 --> 00:32:56,717
The girl has
lost her father

834
00:32:56,755 --> 00:32:58,882
and her freedom,
all in one day.

835
00:32:58,957 --> 00:33:00,254
Master, have you thought

836
00:33:00,292 --> 00:33:03,284
that perhaps this girl could
be the one to break the spell?

837
00:33:03,328 --> 00:33:04,761
Of course l have.

838
00:33:04,796 --> 00:33:06,127
l'm not a fool.

839
00:33:06,164 --> 00:33:07,495
Good!

840
00:33:07,532 --> 00:33:10,296
So, you fall in love with her,
she falls in love with you

841
00:33:10,335 --> 00:33:12,633
and poof!
The spell is broken.

842
00:33:12,671 --> 00:33:14,639
We'll be human again
by midnight.

843
00:33:14,673 --> 00:33:16,470
Ooh, it's not
that easy, Lumiere.

844
00:33:16,508 --> 00:33:17,770
These things take time.

845
00:33:17,809 --> 00:33:19,834
But the rose has already
begun to wilt.

846
00:33:19,911 --> 00:33:21,845
Oh, it's no use.

847
00:33:21,946 --> 00:33:24,710
She's so beautiful, and l'm...

848
00:33:24,749 --> 00:33:25,841
Well, look at me!

849
00:33:28,019 --> 00:33:31,122
Oh, you must help her
to see past all that.

850
00:33:31,122 --> 00:33:32,487
l don't know how.

851
00:33:32,524 --> 00:33:33,855
Well, you can start

852
00:33:33,925 --> 00:33:35,517
by making yourself
more presentable.

853
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:36,754
Straighten up.

854
00:33:36,795 --> 00:33:38,490
Try to act like
a gentleman.

855
00:33:38,530 --> 00:33:39,997
Ah, yes.
When she comes in

856
00:33:40,031 --> 00:33:41,999
give her a dashing,
debonair smile.

857
00:33:42,033 --> 00:33:43,728
Come, come,
show me the smile.

858
00:33:45,003 --> 00:33:46,698
But don't frighten
the poor girl.

859
00:33:46,738 --> 00:33:48,467
lmpress her
with your rapier wit.

860
00:33:48,506 --> 00:33:50,303
But be gentle.

861
00:33:50,342 --> 00:33:51,832
Shower her
with compliments.

862
00:33:51,876 --> 00:33:52,865
But be sincere.

863
00:33:52,911 --> 00:33:53,878
And above all...

864
00:33:53,912 --> 00:33:55,743
BOTH:
You must control your temper!

865
00:33:55,780 --> 00:33:56,872
( doorknob rattling )

866
00:33:56,915 --> 00:34:00,018
Here she is!

867
00:34:00,018 --> 00:34:01,645
Good evening.

868
00:34:01,686 --> 00:34:04,789
Well, where is she?

869
00:34:04,789 --> 00:34:05,778
Who? Oh.

870
00:34:05,824 --> 00:34:06,813
( giggles )

871
00:34:06,925 --> 00:34:08,324
The girl, yes.

872
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:09,588
The... girl.

873
00:34:09,627 --> 00:34:12,824
Well, actually,
she's in the process of...

874
00:34:12,897 --> 00:34:16,492
Circumstances being
what they are...

875
00:34:16,534 --> 00:34:18,058
She's not coming.

876
00:34:18,103 --> 00:34:20,264
What?!

877
00:34:20,305 --> 00:34:21,670
But, your grace...!

878
00:34:21,706 --> 00:34:23,833
Your eminence!

879
00:34:23,942 --> 00:34:25,933
( yelling )

880
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,414
l thought l told you
to come down to dinner!

881
00:34:30,448 --> 00:34:31,779
BELLE:
l'm not hungry.

882
00:34:31,816 --> 00:34:33,784
You come out, or l'll...

883
00:34:33,818 --> 00:34:35,615
l'll... l'll break down
the door!

884
00:34:35,653 --> 00:34:36,813
Master...

885
00:34:36,855 --> 00:34:39,380
l could be wrong,
but that may not be

886
00:34:39,424 --> 00:34:42,359
the best way
to win the girl's affections.

887
00:34:42,394 --> 00:34:45,852
Please attempt
to be a gentleman.

888
00:34:45,964 --> 00:34:48,797
But she is being so difficult.

889
00:34:48,833 --> 00:34:50,425
Gently, gently.

890
00:34:52,737 --> 00:34:54,170
Will you come down to dinner?

891
00:34:54,205 --> 00:34:55,399
No.

892
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:56,702
Hmm?

893
00:34:56,741 --> 00:34:57,833
Ah, ah, ah!

894
00:34:57,876 --> 00:34:59,138
Suave, genteel.

895
00:34:59,177 --> 00:35:02,112
lt would give me
great pleasure

896
00:35:02,147 --> 00:35:04,172
if you would join
me for dinner.

897
00:35:04,249 --> 00:35:05,307
( clearing throat )

898
00:35:05,383 --> 00:35:06,543
( mumbling ):
We say please.

899
00:35:06,584 --> 00:35:08,142
Please.

900
00:35:08,186 --> 00:35:08,982
No, thank you!

901
00:35:09,020 --> 00:35:10,544
You can't stay in there forever!

902
00:35:10,588 --> 00:35:11,919
Yes, l can.

903
00:35:11,956 --> 00:35:15,653
Fine. Then go ahead
and starve!

904
00:35:15,693 --> 00:35:17,957
lf she doesn't eat with me

905
00:35:17,996 --> 00:35:20,521
then she doesn't eat at all.

906
00:35:20,565 --> 00:35:21,554
( roaring )

907
00:35:21,599 --> 00:35:23,499
( door slams )

908
00:35:23,535 --> 00:35:25,002
Oh, dear.

909
00:35:25,036 --> 00:35:26,871
That didn't go very well
at all, did it?

910
00:35:26,871 --> 00:35:29,635
Lumiere, stand watch
at the door

911
00:35:29,674 --> 00:35:31,505
and inform me at once

912
00:35:31,543 --> 00:35:33,238
if there is
the slightest change.

913
00:35:33,311 --> 00:35:35,211
You can count on me,
mon capitan.

914
00:35:35,246 --> 00:35:37,680
Well, we might as well
go downstairs

915
00:35:37,715 --> 00:35:40,707
and start cleaning up.

916
00:35:40,752 --> 00:35:44,347
l ask nicely,
but she refuses.

917
00:35:44,422 --> 00:35:47,152
Well, what does
she want me to do... beg?

918
00:35:48,059 --> 00:35:49,321
Show me the girl.

919
00:35:52,163 --> 00:35:54,028
Well, the master's
really not so bad

920
00:35:54,065 --> 00:35:55,293
once you get
to know him.

921
00:35:55,366 --> 00:35:57,027
Why don't you
give him a chance?

922
00:35:57,068 --> 00:35:58,729
l don't want to
get to know him.

923
00:35:58,770 --> 00:36:00,271
l don't want to
have anything

924
00:36:00,271 --> 00:36:02,000
to do with him!

925
00:36:02,073 --> 00:36:03,870
( groans )

926
00:36:03,908 --> 00:36:05,967
l'm just fooling myself.

927
00:36:06,044 --> 00:36:09,036
She'll never see me
as anything...

928
00:36:09,113 --> 00:36:11,809
but a monster.

929
00:36:15,820 --> 00:36:18,254
lt's hopeless.

930
00:36:35,507 --> 00:36:36,599
GlRL:
Oh, no!

931
00:36:36,641 --> 00:36:37,767
LUMlERE:
Oh, yes!

932
00:36:37,809 --> 00:36:38,798
Oh, no!

933
00:36:38,877 --> 00:36:40,037
Oh, yes, yes, yes!

934
00:36:40,111 --> 00:36:42,375
l've been burned
by you before.

935
00:36:42,413 --> 00:36:43,380
( chuckling )

936
00:36:43,414 --> 00:36:44,642
( gasps )

937
00:36:45,984 --> 00:36:48,043
Zut, alors!
She has emerged!

938
00:36:52,624 --> 00:36:54,285
Come on, Chip,
into the cupboard

939
00:36:54,325 --> 00:36:56,027
with your brothers
and sisters.

940
00:36:56,027 --> 00:36:57,585
( yawning )

941
00:36:57,662 --> 00:36:59,459
But l'm not sleepy.

942
00:36:59,531 --> 00:37:01,123
Yes, you are.

943
00:37:01,165 --> 00:37:03,793
No, l'm not.

944
00:37:03,868 --> 00:37:05,961
l work and l slave all
day long and for what?

945
00:37:06,037 --> 00:37:09,097
A culinary masterpiece
gone to waste.

946
00:37:09,140 --> 00:37:10,368
Oh, stop your grousing.

947
00:37:10,408 --> 00:37:12,399
lt's been a long night
for all of us.

948
00:37:12,443 --> 00:37:15,344
Well, if you ask me,
she was just being stubborn.

949
00:37:15,380 --> 00:37:17,143
After all,
he did say please.

950
00:37:17,181 --> 00:37:19,149
But if the master doesn't learn
to control that temper

951
00:37:19,183 --> 00:37:20,707
he'll never break...

952
00:37:20,785 --> 00:37:22,582
Splendid to see you
out and about, Mademoiselle.

953
00:37:22,620 --> 00:37:26,579
l am Cogsworth,
head of the household.

954
00:37:27,592 --> 00:37:29,890
This is Lumiere.

955
00:37:29,961 --> 00:37:32,156
Enchante, cherie.

956
00:37:32,196 --> 00:37:33,663
lf there's...
Stop that!

957
00:37:33,698 --> 00:37:35,131
...anything we...
Please!

958
00:37:35,166 --> 00:37:37,657
can do to make your
stay more comfortable.

959
00:37:37,702 --> 00:37:38,691
Ow!

960
00:37:38,770 --> 00:37:40,067
l am a little hungry.

961
00:37:40,104 --> 00:37:41,071
You are?

962
00:37:41,105 --> 00:37:42,766
Hear that?
She's hungry.

963
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:43,807
Stoke the fire.

964
00:37:43,841 --> 00:37:44,569
Break out
the silver.

965
00:37:44,609 --> 00:37:46,042
Wake the china.

966
00:37:46,077 --> 00:37:48,602
Remember what the master said.

967
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:49,704
Oh, pishposh.

968
00:37:49,781 --> 00:37:51,908
l'm not about to let
the poor child go hungry.

969
00:37:52,016 --> 00:37:53,108
All right, fine.

970
00:37:53,151 --> 00:37:54,914
Glass of water, crust
of bread, and then...

971
00:37:55,053 --> 00:37:57,422
Cogsworth, l am
surprised at you.

972
00:37:57,422 --> 00:38:00,118
She is not a prisoner.
She's our guest.

973
00:38:00,158 --> 00:38:02,285
We must make her
feel welcome here.

974
00:38:02,327 --> 00:38:04,022
Right this way,
Mademoiselle.

975
00:38:04,095 --> 00:38:05,153
Well, keep it down.

976
00:38:05,196 --> 00:38:07,187
lf the master finds out
about this

977
00:38:07,231 --> 00:38:08,425
it will be
our necks.

978
00:38:08,466 --> 00:38:10,798
Of course, of course.

979
00:38:10,835 --> 00:38:13,633
But what is dinner
without a little music?

980
00:38:13,671 --> 00:38:15,536
Music?

981
00:38:15,607 --> 00:38:18,371
Ma chere
mademoiselle.

982
00:38:18,409 --> 00:38:22,641
lt is with deepest pride
and greatest pleasure

983
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:24,773
that we welcome you tonight.

984
00:38:24,849 --> 00:38:25,873
And now

985
00:38:25,984 --> 00:38:27,349
we invite you
to relax.

986
00:38:27,385 --> 00:38:28,716
Let us
pull up a chair

987
00:38:28,786 --> 00:38:31,414
as the dining room
proudly presents...

988
00:38:31,456 --> 00:38:33,447
your dinner.

989
00:38:35,159 --> 00:38:37,821
* Be... our... guest *

990
00:38:37,862 --> 00:38:39,295
* Be our guest *

991
00:38:39,330 --> 00:38:42,322
* Put our service
to the test *

992
00:38:42,367 --> 00:38:44,198
* Tie your napkin 'round
your neck, cherie *

993
00:38:44,235 --> 00:38:46,863
* And we provide the rest *

994
00:38:46,904 --> 00:38:49,429
* Soup du jour,
Hot hors d'oeuvres *

995
00:38:49,474 --> 00:38:51,339
* Why, we only live
to serve *

996
00:38:51,376 --> 00:38:52,775
* Try the gray stuff *

997
00:38:52,810 --> 00:38:53,936
* lt's delicious *

998
00:38:53,978 --> 00:38:56,242
* Don't believe me,
ask the dishes *

999
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:58,441
* They can sing,
they can dance *

1000
00:38:58,483 --> 00:39:00,815
* After all, Miss,
this is France *

1001
00:39:00,852 --> 00:39:04,879
* And a dinner here
is never second best *

1002
00:39:04,956 --> 00:39:07,424
* Go on, unfold your menu *

1003
00:39:07,458 --> 00:39:09,585
* Take a glance and then *

1004
00:39:09,661 --> 00:39:10,628
* You'll be our guest *

1005
00:39:10,695 --> 00:39:11,855
* Oui, our guest *

1006
00:39:11,896 --> 00:39:13,887
* Be our guest *

1007
00:39:13,931 --> 00:39:16,263
* Beef ragout,
cheese souffle *

1008
00:39:16,300 --> 00:39:18,268
* Pie and pudding
en flambe *

1009
00:39:18,302 --> 00:39:20,361
* We'll prepare and serve
with flair *

1010
00:39:20,405 --> 00:39:22,532
* A culinary cabaret *

1011
00:39:22,573 --> 00:39:24,768
* You're alone
and you're scared *

1012
00:39:24,842 --> 00:39:26,901
* But the banquet's
all prepared *

1013
00:39:26,978 --> 00:39:28,912
* No one's gloomy
or complaining *

1014
00:39:28,946 --> 00:39:31,073
* While the flatware's
entertaining *

1015
00:39:31,115 --> 00:39:33,310
* We tell jokes,
l do tricks *

1016
00:39:33,351 --> 00:39:35,615
* With my fellow candlesticks *

1017
00:39:35,687 --> 00:39:39,623
* And it's all in perfect taste,
that you can bet *

1018
00:39:39,691 --> 00:39:41,716
* Come on and lift your glass *

1019
00:39:41,793 --> 00:39:43,420
* You've won your own
free pass *

1020
00:39:43,461 --> 00:39:44,553
* To be our guest-- *

1021
00:39:44,595 --> 00:39:46,062
* lf you're stressed *

1022
00:39:46,097 --> 00:39:48,224
* lt's fine dining
we suggest-- *

1023
00:39:48,266 --> 00:39:50,632
* Be our guest,
be our guest *

1024
00:39:50,702 --> 00:39:52,465
* Be our guest! *

1025
00:39:52,503 --> 00:39:55,802
( mournfully ):
* Life is so unnerving *

1026
00:39:55,873 --> 00:39:58,865
* For a servant
who's not serving *

1027
00:39:58,910 --> 00:40:02,141
* He's not whole
without a soul to wait upon *

1028
00:40:02,180 --> 00:40:03,943
Get off!

1029
00:40:04,048 --> 00:40:07,484
-( sleigh bells jingling )
-* Ah, those good old days
when we were useful *

1030
00:40:07,518 --> 00:40:09,042
Huh?

1031
00:40:09,087 --> 00:40:11,078
* Suddenly, those good
old days are gone *

1032
00:40:11,122 --> 00:40:13,955
( groans ):
Oh!

1033
00:40:14,025 --> 00:40:15,959
* Ten years
we've been rusting *

1034
00:40:15,993 --> 00:40:18,291
* Needing so much more
than dusting *

1035
00:40:18,329 --> 00:40:20,354
* Needing exercise *

1036
00:40:20,398 --> 00:40:21,956
* A chance
to use our skills *

1037
00:40:21,999 --> 00:40:23,432
( howling )

1038
00:40:23,468 --> 00:40:27,199
* Most days we just
lay around the castle *

1039
00:40:27,238 --> 00:40:28,227
( grunting )

1040
00:40:28,272 --> 00:40:29,739
* Flabby, fat and lazy *

1041
00:40:29,774 --> 00:40:31,867
* You walked in
and oops-a-daisy! *

1042
00:40:31,909 --> 00:40:33,774
* lt's a guest, it's a guest! *

1043
00:40:33,845 --> 00:40:35,608
* Sakes alive,
well, l'll be blessed *

1044
00:40:35,646 --> 00:40:37,671
* Wine's been poured, *
And thank the lord *

1045
00:40:37,749 --> 00:40:39,614
* l've had the napkins
freshly pressed *

1046
00:40:39,650 --> 00:40:41,982
* With dessert,
she'll want tea *

1047
00:40:42,086 --> 00:40:43,576
* And, my dear,
that's fine with me *

1048
00:40:43,621 --> 00:40:45,748
* While the cups
do their soft-shoeing *

1049
00:40:45,823 --> 00:40:47,814
* l'll be bubbling,
l'll be brewing *

1050
00:40:47,859 --> 00:40:49,622
* l'll get warm,
piping hot *

1051
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:51,753
* Heaven's sake,
is that a spot? *

1052
00:40:51,829 --> 00:40:54,525
* Clean it up, we want
the company impressed *

1053
00:40:54,565 --> 00:40:56,726
* We've got a lot to do *

1054
00:40:56,801 --> 00:40:58,598
* ls it one lump or two? *

1055
00:40:58,636 --> 00:40:59,364
* For you, our guest *

1056
00:40:59,403 --> 00:41:00,529
* She's our guest *

1057
00:41:00,571 --> 00:41:01,799
* She's our guest *

1058
00:41:01,873 --> 00:41:03,363
* She's our guest *

1059
00:41:03,407 --> 00:41:06,069
People, fun's over,
over here, line up...

1060
00:41:06,110 --> 00:41:07,475
( screams )

1061
00:41:07,512 --> 00:41:09,412
* lt's ten years since
we've had anybody here *

1062
00:41:09,447 --> 00:41:10,436
* And we're obsessed *

1063
00:41:10,481 --> 00:41:12,711
* With your meal,
with your ease *

1064
00:41:12,784 --> 00:41:14,581
* Yes, indeed,
we aim to please *

1065
00:41:14,619 --> 00:41:16,951
* While the candlelight's
still glowing *

1066
00:41:17,054 --> 00:41:21,388
* Let us help you,
we'll keep going *

1067
00:41:21,425 --> 00:41:25,623
* Course... by... course *

1068
00:41:25,663 --> 00:41:27,722
* One by one *

1069
00:41:27,799 --> 00:41:30,427
* Till you shout,
''Enough, l'm done!'' *

1070
00:41:30,468 --> 00:41:34,802
* Then we'll sing you
off to sleep as you digest *

1071
00:41:34,872 --> 00:41:36,931
* Tonight you'll prop
your feet up *

1072
00:41:36,974 --> 00:41:38,532
* But for now, let's eat up *

1073
00:41:38,576 --> 00:41:42,706
* Be our guest,
be our guest *

1074
00:41:42,747 --> 00:41:44,578
* Be our guest *

1075
00:41:44,615 --> 00:41:53,080
* Please be our guest! *

1076
00:41:55,359 --> 00:41:56,485
Bravo!

1077
00:41:56,527 --> 00:41:57,858
That was wonderful.

1078
00:41:57,929 --> 00:41:58,987
Thank you.

1079
00:41:59,030 --> 00:42:01,191
Thank you, Mademoiselle.

1080
00:42:01,232 --> 00:42:03,132
Good show, wasn't it?

1081
00:42:03,167 --> 00:42:04,600
Yes, everyone.

1082
00:42:04,635 --> 00:42:07,934
My goodness, look at the time.

1083
00:42:08,005 --> 00:42:09,870
Now it's off to bed,
off to bed.

1084
00:42:09,941 --> 00:42:12,432
Oh, l couldn't possibly
go to bed now.

