00:56:42,879 --> 00:56:44,073
( barking )

1354
00:56:44,114 --> 00:56:45,081
( yells )

1355
00:56:45,115 --> 00:56:46,548
Oh, lighten up, Cogsworth

1356
00:56:46,583 --> 00:56:48,551
and let nature take its course.

1357
00:56:48,585 --> 00:56:51,281
lt's obvious there's
a spark between them.

1358
00:56:51,354 --> 00:56:55,290
Yes, but there's no harm
in fanning the flames.

1359
00:56:55,325 --> 00:56:57,127
You know... a little.

1360
00:56:57,127 --> 00:56:58,321
Besides, they must fall in love

1361
00:56:58,395 --> 00:57:00,158
tonight if we ever expect
to be human again.

1362
00:57:00,230 --> 00:57:01,629
Ah, human again.

1363
00:57:01,665 --> 00:57:03,189
Human again.

1364
00:57:03,266 --> 00:57:06,258
Yes, think
what that means.

1365
00:57:06,336 --> 00:57:09,169
( bells tolling )

1366
00:57:09,206 --> 00:57:11,800
* l'll be cooking again *

1367
00:57:11,842 --> 00:57:13,742
* Be good looking again *

1368
00:57:13,777 --> 00:57:17,543
* With a mademoiselle
on each arm *

1369
00:57:17,581 --> 00:57:20,243
* When l'm human again *

1370
00:57:20,317 --> 00:57:21,978
* Only human again *

1371
00:57:22,018 --> 00:57:25,476
* Poised and polished
and gleaming with charm *

1372
00:57:25,522 --> 00:57:27,251
* l'll be courting again *

1373
00:57:27,324 --> 00:57:29,224
* Chic and sporting again *

1374
00:57:29,259 --> 00:57:32,228
* Which should cause
several husbands alarm *

1375
00:57:32,262 --> 00:57:34,924
* Ha, ha!
l'll hop down off this shelf *

1376
00:57:34,965 --> 00:57:36,830
* And tout de suite be myself *

1377
00:57:36,867 --> 00:57:39,927
* l can't wait
to be human again *

1378
00:57:41,905 --> 00:57:44,066
* When we're human again *

1379
00:57:44,141 --> 00:57:45,938
* Only human again *

1380
00:57:45,976 --> 00:57:48,877
* When we're knickknacks
and whatnots no more *

1381
00:57:48,912 --> 00:57:53,713
* When we're human again,
good and human again *

1382
00:57:53,784 --> 00:57:56,309
* Oh, cherie,
won't it all be top drawer? *

1383
00:57:56,386 --> 00:57:58,354
* l'll wear lipstick and rouge *

1384
00:57:58,421 --> 00:57:59,718
* And l won't be so huge *

1385
00:57:59,790 --> 00:58:03,385
* Why, l'll easily fit
through that door *

1386
00:58:03,426 --> 00:58:05,291
* l'll exude savoir faire *

1387
00:58:05,362 --> 00:58:07,330
* l'll wear gowns,
l'll have hair *

1388
00:58:07,364 --> 00:58:10,458
* lt's my prayer
to be human again *

1389
00:58:10,500 --> 00:58:13,230
( crashing )

1390
00:58:15,605 --> 00:58:17,197
* When we're human again *

1391
00:58:17,274 --> 00:58:19,139
* Only human again *

1392
00:58:19,176 --> 00:58:22,475
* When the world once more
starts making sense *

1393
00:58:22,512 --> 00:58:24,139
* l'll unwind, for a change *

1394
00:58:24,214 --> 00:58:25,738
* Really? That'd be strange *

1395
00:58:25,816 --> 00:58:29,047
* Can l help it
if l'm t-t-tense? *

1396
00:58:29,085 --> 00:58:30,518
* ln a shack by the sea *

1397
00:58:30,554 --> 00:58:32,317
* l'll sit back, sipping tea *

1398
00:58:32,389 --> 00:58:35,688
* Let my early
retirement commence *

1399
00:58:35,725 --> 00:58:37,420
* Far from fools made of wax *

1400
00:58:37,460 --> 00:58:41,157
* l'll get down to brass tacks
and relax! *

1401
00:58:41,231 --> 00:58:44,962
* When l'm human again *

1402
00:58:45,001 --> 00:58:48,459
* So sweep the dust
from the floor *

1403
00:58:48,505 --> 00:58:52,032
* Let's let some light
in the room *

1404
00:58:52,142 --> 00:58:53,734
* l can feel, l can tell *

1405
00:58:53,777 --> 00:58:56,837
* Someone might break the spell
any day now *

1406
00:58:56,880 --> 00:58:58,507
( barking )

1407
00:58:58,548 --> 00:59:02,006
* Shine up the brass
on the door *

1408
00:59:02,085 --> 00:59:04,918
* Alert the dust pail
and broom *

1409
00:59:04,955 --> 00:59:06,980
* lf it all goes as planned *

1410
00:59:07,057 --> 00:59:12,393
* Our time may be at hand
any day now *

1411
00:59:12,462 --> 00:59:15,795
* Open the shutters,
and let in some air *

1412
00:59:15,866 --> 00:59:19,802
* Put these here,
and put those over there *

1413
00:59:19,870 --> 00:59:23,271
* Sweep up the years
of sadness and tears *

1414
00:59:23,306 --> 00:59:26,002
* And throw them away *

1415
00:59:26,042 --> 00:59:27,771
( clears throat )

1416
00:59:32,148 --> 00:59:34,878
* We'll be human again *

1417
00:59:34,918 --> 00:59:37,079
* Only human again *

1418
00:59:37,120 --> 00:59:39,782
* When the girl
finally sets us all free *

1419
00:59:39,823 --> 00:59:42,383
* Cheeks a-blooming again *

1420
00:59:42,459 --> 00:59:44,324
* We're assuming again *

1421
00:59:44,361 --> 00:59:47,330
* We'll resume our
long lost joie de vivre *

1422
00:59:47,364 --> 00:59:48,524
* We'll be playing again *

1423
00:59:48,565 --> 00:59:50,897
* Holidaying again *

1424
00:59:50,934 --> 00:59:52,959
* And we're praying
it's ASAP *

1425
00:59:53,003 --> 00:59:54,061
( cat snarls )

1426
00:59:54,137 --> 00:59:56,105
* We will push, we will shove *

1427
00:59:56,239 --> 00:59:58,070
* They will both fall in love *

1428
00:59:58,174 --> 01:00:01,974
* And we'll finally
be human again... *

1429
01:00:03,580 --> 01:00:06,071
For never was a story
of more woe

1430
01:00:06,116 --> 01:00:08,676
Than this of Juliet
and her Romeo.

1431
01:00:08,718 --> 01:00:10,083
( sighs )

1432
01:00:10,153 --> 01:00:12,621
Could you read it again?

1433
01:00:12,656 --> 01:00:14,817
Well, here, why don't
you read it to me?

1434
01:00:14,858 --> 01:00:17,053
Uh, all right.

1435
01:00:17,093 --> 01:00:19,960
Uh...

1436
01:00:19,996 --> 01:00:22,089
Uh... l can't.

1437
01:00:22,132 --> 01:00:24,828
You mean,
you never learned?

1438
01:00:24,868 --> 01:00:27,098
l learned... a little.

1439
01:00:27,170 --> 01:00:29,798
lt's just been so long.

1440
01:00:29,839 --> 01:00:32,103
Well, here, l'll help you.

1441
01:00:32,208 --> 01:00:33,732
Let's start here.

1442
01:00:33,777 --> 01:00:36,507
Here.

1443
01:00:36,546 --> 01:00:38,514
Okay, ''Twoe...''

1444
01:00:38,548 --> 01:00:39,515
''Two.''

1445
01:00:39,549 --> 01:00:41,676
''Two... l knew that.

1446
01:00:41,718 --> 01:00:44,380
Two households...''

1447
01:00:44,454 --> 01:00:48,481
* We'll be dancing again *

1448
01:00:48,525 --> 01:00:50,186
* We'll be twirling again *

1449
01:00:50,260 --> 01:00:53,752
* We'll be whirling around
with such ease *

1450
01:00:53,797 --> 01:00:55,128
* When we're human again *

1451
01:00:55,231 --> 01:00:56,823
* Only human again *

1452
01:00:56,866 --> 01:01:00,529
* We'll go waltzing
those old one, two, threes *

1453
01:01:00,570 --> 01:01:02,504
* We'll be floating again *

1454
01:01:02,539 --> 01:01:03,801
* We'll be gliding again *

1455
01:01:03,840 --> 01:01:07,503
* Stepping, striding
as fine as you please *

1456
01:01:07,544 --> 01:01:10,877
* Like a real human does *

1457
01:01:10,914 --> 01:01:14,441
* l'll be all that l was *

1458
01:01:14,517 --> 01:01:19,011
* On that glorious morn
when we're finally reborn *

1459
01:01:19,089 --> 01:01:22,616
* And we're all *

1460
01:01:22,659 --> 01:01:27,892
* Human again! *

1461
01:01:35,605 --> 01:01:37,368
( sighing )

1462
01:01:37,440 --> 01:01:40,568
( growls )

1463
01:01:40,610 --> 01:01:43,579
Tonight is
the night.

1464
01:01:43,613 --> 01:01:46,377
l'm not sure l can do this.

1465
01:01:46,449 --> 01:01:48,041
You don't have time to be timid.

1466
01:01:48,084 --> 01:01:50,314
You must be bold, daring.

1467
01:01:50,387 --> 01:01:52,116
Bold, daring.

1468
01:01:55,025 --> 01:01:57,289
There will be music...

1469
01:01:57,327 --> 01:01:59,693
romantic candlelight...

1470
01:01:59,729 --> 01:02:01,697
provided by myself.

1471
01:02:01,731 --> 01:02:03,221
And when the moment
is right

1472
01:02:03,299 --> 01:02:05,062
you confess your love.

1473
01:02:05,101 --> 01:02:07,069
Yes, l con...

1474
01:02:07,137 --> 01:02:09,935
l-l... No, l can't.

1475
01:02:09,973 --> 01:02:11,440
You care for the girl,
don't you?

1476
01:02:11,474 --> 01:02:13,704
More than anything.

1477
01:02:13,743 --> 01:02:15,472
Well, then,
you must tell her.

1478
01:02:17,547 --> 01:02:18,878
Voila!

1479
01:02:18,915 --> 01:02:21,281
Oh, you look so... so...

1480
01:02:21,317 --> 01:02:23,251
Stupid.

1481
01:02:23,286 --> 01:02:26,380
Not quite the word
l was looking for.

1482
01:02:26,456 --> 01:02:28,447
Perhaps a little more
off the top?

1483
01:02:29,926 --> 01:02:30,858
( clearing throat )

1484
01:02:30,894 --> 01:02:34,261
Your lady awaits.

1485
01:02:34,297 --> 01:02:36,094
( chuckles )

1486
01:02:47,811 --> 01:02:50,177
( clears throat )

1487
01:02:58,888 --> 01:03:04,155
* Tale as old as time *

1488
01:03:04,194 --> 01:03:08,358
* True as it can be *

1489
01:03:08,431 --> 01:03:09,523
( barking )

1490
01:03:09,599 --> 01:03:12,568
* Barely even friends *

1491
01:03:12,602 --> 01:03:15,196
* Then somebody bends *

1492
01:03:15,271 --> 01:03:17,136
* Unexpectedly *

1493
01:03:18,842 --> 01:03:21,538
* Just a little change *

1494
01:03:24,681 --> 01:03:27,309
* Small, to say the least *

1495
01:03:27,383 --> 01:03:29,943
* Both a little scared *

1496
01:03:29,986 --> 01:03:33,183
* Neither one prepared *

1497
01:03:33,223 --> 01:03:35,953
* Beauty and the Beast *

1498
01:03:37,160 --> 01:03:38,821
( gulps )

1499
01:03:38,862 --> 01:03:40,727
* Ever just the same *

1500
01:03:43,867 --> 01:03:46,461
* Ever a surprise *

1501
01:03:46,536 --> 01:03:48,629
Huh? Huh? Huh?

1502
01:03:48,705 --> 01:03:51,401
* Ever as before *

1503
01:03:51,474 --> 01:03:53,840
* Ever just as sure *

1504
01:03:53,877 --> 01:03:57,404
* As the sun will rise *

1505
01:03:58,915 --> 01:04:03,648
* Tale as old as time *

1506
01:04:03,720 --> 01:04:08,282
* Tune as old as song *

1507
01:04:08,358 --> 01:04:11,521
* Bittersweet and strange *

1508
01:04:11,594 --> 01:04:14,028
* Finding you can change *

1509
01:04:14,164 --> 01:04:17,031
* Learning you were wrong *

1510
01:04:19,002 --> 01:04:23,701
* Certain as the sun *

1511
01:04:23,740 --> 01:04:26,641
* Rising in the east *

1512
01:04:26,676 --> 01:04:28,906
* Tale as old as time *

1513
01:04:28,945 --> 01:04:31,709
* Song as old as rhyme *

1514
01:04:31,748 --> 01:04:34,774
* Beauty and the Beast *

1515
01:04:34,817 --> 01:04:36,580
Shh!

1516
01:04:37,720 --> 01:04:41,315
* Tale as old as time *

1517
01:04:41,391 --> 01:04:45,555
* Song as old as rhyme *

1518
01:04:45,628 --> 01:04:52,727
* Beauty and the Beast. *

1519
01:04:52,769 --> 01:04:54,930
Off to the cupboard
with you now, Chip.

1520
01:04:54,971 --> 01:04:56,336
lt's past your bedtime.

1521
01:04:56,372 --> 01:04:58,670
( yawns )

1522
01:04:58,708 --> 01:05:01,108
Good night, love.

1523
01:05:10,053 --> 01:05:13,853
( insects humming )

1524
01:05:24,567 --> 01:05:28,025
Belle?

1525
01:05:28,104 --> 01:05:31,665
Are you... happy
here with me?

1526
01:05:31,741 --> 01:05:33,572
Yes.

1527
01:05:37,647 --> 01:05:40,047
What is it?

1528
01:05:40,116 --> 01:05:42,812
lf only l could see
my father again

1529
01:05:42,852 --> 01:05:44,479
just for a moment.

1530
01:05:44,554 --> 01:05:45,919
l miss him so much.

1531
01:05:51,561 --> 01:05:54,496
There is a way.

1532
01:05:55,698 --> 01:05:58,223
This mirror will show
you anything...

1533
01:05:58,301 --> 01:06:01,702
anything
you wish to see.

1534
01:06:01,771 --> 01:06:04,569
l'd like to see
my father, please.

1535
01:06:09,212 --> 01:06:11,442
( coughs )

1536
01:06:11,514 --> 01:06:12,674
Papa?

1537
01:06:12,715 --> 01:06:13,943
Oh, no.

1538
01:06:13,983 --> 01:06:16,281
He's sick.

1539
01:06:16,319 --> 01:06:17,911
He may be dying

1540
01:06:17,954 --> 01:06:19,922
and he's all alone.

1541
01:06:25,128 --> 01:06:28,586
Then, you must go to him.

1542
01:06:28,665 --> 01:06:29,927
What did you say?

1543
01:06:29,966 --> 01:06:31,024
l release you.

1544
01:06:31,067 --> 01:06:33,535
You are no longer my prisoner.

1545
01:06:33,569 --> 01:06:34,968
You mean...

1546
01:06:35,004 --> 01:06:36,164
l'm free?

1547
01:06:36,205 --> 01:06:38,264
Yes.

1548
01:06:38,341 --> 01:06:40,502
Oh, thank you.

1549
01:06:40,576 --> 01:06:42,703
Hold on, Papa.

1550
01:06:42,745 --> 01:06:45,009
l'm on my way.

1551
01:06:45,048 --> 01:06:46,845
Take it with you

1552
01:06:46,883 --> 01:06:51,320
so you'll always have
a way to look back

1553
01:06:51,354 --> 01:06:53,151
and remember me.

1554
01:06:55,825 --> 01:06:57,417
Thank you for
understanding

1555
01:06:57,493 --> 01:06:58,790
how much he needs me.

1556
01:07:07,470 --> 01:07:09,597
Well, Your Highness,
l must say

1557
01:07:09,672 --> 01:07:12,197
everything is going
just swimmingly.

1558
01:07:12,241 --> 01:07:13,435
l knew you had it in you.

1559
01:07:13,476 --> 01:07:14,704
( laughs )

1560
01:07:14,777 --> 01:07:16,244
l let her go.

1561
01:07:16,279 --> 01:07:17,576
( chuckles )

1562
01:07:17,647 --> 01:07:18,944
Yes, yes.

1563
01:07:18,981 --> 01:07:20,005
Splen...

1564
01:07:20,116 --> 01:07:23,017
You what?

1565
01:07:23,086 --> 01:07:24,576
How could you do that?

1566
01:07:24,654 --> 01:07:26,019
l had to.

1567
01:07:26,122 --> 01:07:27,111
Yes, but...

1568
01:07:27,156 --> 01:07:28,123
( sputtering )

1569
01:07:28,157 --> 01:07:29,021
Why?

1570
01:07:29,125 --> 01:07:32,822
Because... l love her.

1571
01:07:32,862 --> 01:07:34,352
ALL:
He did what?

1572
01:07:34,430 --> 01:07:35,590
Yes.

1573
01:07:35,665 --> 01:07:37,360
l'm afraid it's true.

1574
01:07:37,400 --> 01:07:38,799
She's going away?

1575
01:07:38,835 --> 01:07:40,894
But he was so close.

1576
01:07:40,937 --> 01:07:42,666
After all this time

1577
01:07:42,739 --> 01:07:45,435
he's finally learned to love.

1578
01:07:45,475 --> 01:07:48,137
That's it, then.
That should break the spell.

1579
01:07:48,177 --> 01:07:49,735
But it's not enough.

1580
01:07:49,812 --> 01:07:52,178
She has to love him
in return.

1581
01:07:52,215 --> 01:07:55,548
COGSWORTH:
Now it's too late.

1582
01:07:56,586 --> 01:07:57,883
( roaring )

1583
01:08:04,026 --> 01:08:06,859
Papa! Papa!

1584
01:08:08,097 --> 01:08:09,428
( gasping )

1585
01:08:19,776 --> 01:08:21,971
Ooh.

1586
01:08:22,011 --> 01:08:24,138
They're back.

1587
01:08:25,448 --> 01:08:26,676
Belle?

1588
01:08:26,749 --> 01:08:27,716
Shh.

1589
01:08:27,784 --> 01:08:29,149
lt's all right, Papa.

1590
01:08:29,185 --> 01:08:31,278
l'm home.

1591
01:08:31,320 --> 01:08:32,514
l thought l'd never

1592
01:08:32,588 --> 01:08:35,113
see you again.

1593
01:08:35,158 --> 01:08:37,023
l missed you so much.

1594
01:08:37,093 --> 01:08:38,025
but the Beast?

1595
01:08:38,094 --> 01:08:40,028
Did you...
How did you escape?

1596
01:08:40,062 --> 01:08:41,359
l didn't escape, Papa.

1597
01:08:41,431 --> 01:08:42,625
He let me go.

1598
01:08:42,698 --> 01:08:44,029
That horrible beast?

1599
01:08:44,133 --> 01:08:47,159
But he's different now, Papa.

1600
01:08:47,203 --> 01:08:49,501
He's changed somehow.

1601
01:08:53,543 --> 01:08:54,737
Hi.

1602
01:08:54,811 --> 01:08:57,712
Oh. A stowaway.

1603
01:08:57,747 --> 01:09:01,183
Why, hello there, little fella.

1604
01:09:01,217 --> 01:09:03,014
Didn't think
l'd see you again.

1605
01:09:03,052 --> 01:09:04,542
Belle, why'd you go away?

1606
01:09:04,620 --> 01:09:06,178
Don't you like us anymore?

1607
01:09:06,222 --> 01:09:08,349
Oh, Chip, of course l do.

1608
01:09:08,391 --> 01:09:09,722
lt's just...

1609
01:09:09,792 --> 01:09:14,363
( knocking )

1610
01:09:14,363 --> 01:09:15,557
May l help you?

1611
01:09:15,631 --> 01:09:17,565
l've come to collect
your father.

1612
01:09:17,600 --> 01:09:19,067
My father?

1613
01:09:19,101 --> 01:09:21,069
Don't worry, Mademoiselle.

1614
01:09:21,103 --> 01:09:23,298
We'll take good care of him.

1615
01:09:24,707 --> 01:09:25,833
My father's not crazy.

1616
01:09:25,875 --> 01:09:27,706
He was raving like a lunatic.

1617
01:09:27,777 --> 01:09:29,574
We all heard him, didn't we?

1618
01:09:29,612 --> 01:09:31,546
( all agreeing )

1619
01:09:32,548 --> 01:09:34,072
No, l won't let you.

1620
01:09:34,150 --> 01:09:35,082
Belle?

1621
01:09:35,117 --> 01:09:37,779
Maurice, tell us again, old man.

1622
01:09:37,854 --> 01:09:39,822
Just how big
was the beast?

1623
01:09:39,856 --> 01:09:41,517
( chuckles )

1624
01:09:41,591 --> 01:09:45,083
He was... l mean, he was...
he was... enormous.

1625
01:09:45,194 --> 01:09:46,889
l-l'd say
at least eight...

1626
01:09:46,929 --> 01:09:48,328
No, more like ten feet.

1627
01:09:48,364 --> 01:09:49,331
( laughing )

1628
01:09:49,365 --> 01:09:53,426
Well, you don't get
much crazier than that.

1629
01:09:53,503 --> 01:09:54,697
( all laughing )

1630
01:09:54,770 --> 01:09:56,931
lt's true, l tell you.

1631
01:09:56,973 --> 01:09:58,907
Get him
out of here.

1632
01:09:58,941 --> 01:10:00,272
Let go of me.

1633
01:10:00,309 --> 01:10:01,401
No!

1634
01:10:01,444 --> 01:10:03,503
You can't do this.

1635
01:10:03,579 --> 01:10:04,705
Poor Belle.

1636
01:10:04,780 --> 01:10:07,214
lt's a shame
about your father.

1637
01:10:07,250 --> 01:10:08,979
You know he's
not crazy, Gaston.

1638
01:10:09,018 --> 01:10:11,919
Hmm, l might be able
to clear up this...

1639
01:10:11,954 --> 01:10:13,683
little misunderstanding.

1640
01:10:13,756 --> 01:10:14,814
lf...

1641
01:10:14,891 --> 01:10:15,687
lf what?

1642
01:10:15,758 --> 01:10:17,692
lf you marry me.

1643
01:10:17,727 --> 01:10:18,694
What?

1644
01:10:18,728 --> 01:10:20,355
One little word, Belle.
That's all it takes.

1645
01:10:20,396 --> 01:10:21,385
Never.

1646
01:10:21,430 --> 01:10:23,057
Have it your way.

1647
01:10:23,132 --> 01:10:23,928
Belle.

1648
01:10:25,635 --> 01:10:27,159
Let go of me.

1649
01:10:27,203 --> 01:10:28,670
My father's not crazy

1650
01:10:28,704 --> 01:10:29,830
and l can prove it.

1651
01:10:29,906 --> 01:10:32,101
Show me the Beast.

1652
01:10:33,743 --> 01:10:35,335
( roaring )

1653
01:10:35,378 --> 01:10:36,709
( crowd gasping )

1654
01:10:36,779 --> 01:10:38,076
WOMAN:
ls it dangerous?

1655
01:10:38,147 --> 01:10:40,945
Oh, no, no, he'd
never hurt anyone.

1656
01:10:40,983 --> 01:10:43,417
Please, l know he looks vicious

1657
01:10:43,452 --> 01:10:45,079
but he's really
kind and gentle.

1658
01:10:45,187 --> 01:10:46,711
He's my friend.

1659
01:10:46,789 --> 01:10:47,949
lf l didn't know better

1660
01:10:47,990 --> 01:10:50,550
l'd think you had feelings
for this monster.

1661
01:10:50,626 --> 01:10:53,117
He's no monster, Gaston.
You are.

1662
01:10:54,330 --> 01:10:57,366
She's as crazy
as the old man.

1663
01:10:57,366 --> 01:11:00,733
The Beast will make off
with your children.

1664
01:11:00,803 --> 01:11:01,667
-He'll come after them
in the night.
-No!

1665
01:11:01,704 --> 01:11:02,671
We're not safe

1666
01:11:02,705 --> 01:11:04,229
till his head
is mounted on my wall.

1667
01:11:04,273 --> 01:11:06,036
l say we kill the Beast!

1668
01:11:06,142 --> 01:11:07,040
( cheering )

1669
01:11:07,109 --> 01:11:08,906
* We're not safe
until he's dead *

1670
01:11:08,945 --> 01:11:10,537
* He'll come stalking us
at night *

1671
01:11:10,613 --> 01:11:12,478
* Set to sacrifice
our children *

1672
01:11:12,515 --> 01:11:14,278
* To his monstrous appetite *

1673
01:11:14,317 --> 01:11:16,148
* He'll wreak havoc
on our village *

1674
01:11:16,185 --> 01:11:17,709
* lf we let him wander free *

1675
01:11:17,787 --> 01:11:21,450
* So it's time to take
some action, boys *

1676
01:11:21,490 --> 01:11:26,621
* lt's time to follow me *

1677
01:11:26,696 --> 01:11:28,323
( cheering )

1678
01:11:28,364 --> 01:11:30,229
* Through the mist,
through the woods *

1679
01:11:30,266 --> 01:11:32,063
* Through the darkness
and the shadows *

1680
01:11:32,168 --> 01:11:34,534
* lt's a nightmare,
but it's one exciting ride *

1681
01:11:34,604 --> 01:11:38,005
* Say a prayer, then we're there
at the drawbridge of a castle *

1682
01:11:38,040 --> 01:11:41,476
* And there's something
truly terrible inside *

1683
01:11:41,510 --> 01:11:44,206
* lt's a beast, he's got fangs,
razor-sharp ones *

1684
01:11:44,246 --> 01:11:47,613
* Massive paws, killer claws
for the feast *

1685
01:11:47,650 --> 01:11:49,618
* Hear him roar, see him foam *

1686
01:11:49,652 --> 01:11:51,313
* But we're not coming home *

1687
01:11:51,354 --> 01:11:52,787
* Till he's dead *

1688
01:11:52,822 --> 01:11:54,517
* Good and dead *

1689
01:11:54,557 --> 01:11:55,649
* Kill the Beast! *

1690
01:11:55,725 --> 01:11:57,283
No, l won't
let you do this.

1691
01:11:57,326 --> 01:11:59,851
lf you're not with us,
you're against us.

1692
01:11:59,929 --> 01:12:00,953
Bring the old man.

1693
01:12:00,997 --> 01:12:02,624
Get your hands off me.

1694
01:12:02,698 --> 01:12:05,030
We can't have them running off
to warn the creature.

1695
01:12:05,134 --> 01:12:06,396
Let us out!

1696
01:12:06,435 --> 01:12:09,131
We'll rid the village
of this beast.

1697
01:12:09,171 --> 01:12:10,195
Who's with me?

1698
01:12:10,239 --> 01:12:11,797
( cheering )

1699
01:12:11,874 --> 01:12:13,865
* Raise your torch,
mount your horse *

1700
01:12:13,943 --> 01:12:16,241
* Screw your courage
to the sticking place *

1701
01:12:16,278 --> 01:12:18,746
* We're counting on Gaston
to lead the way *

1702
01:12:18,781 --> 01:12:20,544
* Through the mist,
through the wood *

1703
01:12:20,583 --> 01:12:22,210
* Where,
within a haunted castle *

1704
01:12:22,251 --> 01:12:24,879
* Something's lurking
that you don't see every day *

1705
01:12:24,954 --> 01:12:28,481
* lt's a beast,
one as tall as a mountain *

1706
01:12:28,524 --> 01:12:31,687
* We won't rest
till he's good and deceased *

1707
01:12:31,761 --> 01:12:33,524
* Sally forth, tally ho *

1708
01:12:33,562 --> 01:12:35,189
* Grab your sword,
grab your bow *

1709
01:12:35,231 --> 01:12:36,721
* Praise the lord,
and here we go. *

1710
01:12:36,799 --> 01:12:40,200
We'll lay siege to the castle
and bring back his head!

1711
01:12:40,236 --> 01:12:42,500
l have to warn the Beast.

1712
01:12:42,538 --> 01:12:44,438
This is all my fault.

1713
01:12:44,473 --> 01:12:46,407
Oh, Papa, what are
we going to do?

1714
01:12:46,442 --> 01:12:47,773
Now, now.

1715
01:12:47,843 --> 01:12:49,333
We'll think of something.

1716
01:12:52,415 --> 01:12:53,609
Ah!

1717
01:12:55,217 --> 01:12:56,514
( thunder claps )

1718
01:12:56,552 --> 01:12:58,952
* We don't like
what we don't understand *

1719
01:12:58,988 --> 01:13:00,717
* ln fact, it scares us *

1720
01:13:00,790 --> 01:13:03,350
* And this monster
is mysterious at least *

1721
01:13:03,392 --> 01:13:04,882
* Bring your guns,
bring your knives *

1722
01:13:04,960 --> 01:13:06,450
* Save your children
and your wives *

1723
01:13:06,495 --> 01:13:09,589
* We'll save our village
and our lives *

1724
01:13:09,632 --> 01:13:11,031
* We'll kill the Beast! *

1725
01:13:11,133 --> 01:13:12,532
COGSWORTH:
l knew it.

1726
01:13:12,568 --> 01:13:14,968
l knew it was foolish
to get our hopes up.

1727
01:13:15,004 --> 01:13:17,768
Maybe it would have been better
if she'd never come at all.

1728
01:13:17,840 --> 01:13:19,034
( barking )

1729
01:13:19,075 --> 01:13:20,303
Could it be?

1730
01:13:20,342 --> 01:13:21,138
ls it she?

1731
01:13:21,177 --> 01:13:22,576
Sacre bleu!

1732
01:13:22,611 --> 01:13:23,635
lnvaders.

1733
01:13:23,713 --> 01:13:24,907
COGSWORTH:
Encroachers.

1734
01:13:24,980 --> 01:13:26,311
POTTS:
And they have
the mirror.

1735
01:13:26,348 --> 01:13:27,372
Warn the master.

1736
01:13:27,416 --> 01:13:29,350
lf it's a fight they want,
we'll be ready for them.

1737
01:13:29,385 --> 01:13:30,374
Who's with me?

1738
01:13:30,419 --> 01:13:31,408
Ah!

1739
01:13:31,454 --> 01:13:33,445
Take whatever booty
you can find

1740
01:13:33,489 --> 01:13:36,583
but remember,
the Beast is mine!

1741
01:13:36,625 --> 01:13:38,354
* Lights ablaze, banners high *

1742
01:13:38,394 --> 01:13:40,055
* We go marching into battle *

1743
01:13:40,129 --> 01:13:42,825
* Unafraid, although
the danger just increased *

1744
01:13:42,898 --> 01:13:44,593
* Raise the flag,
sing the song *

1745
01:13:44,633 --> 01:13:45,964
* Here we come,
we're 50 strong *

1746
01:13:46,035 --> 01:13:48,526
* And 50 Frenchmen
can't be wrong *

1747
01:13:48,571 --> 01:13:50,368
* Let's kill the Beast! *

1748
01:13:51,340 --> 01:13:54,503
-Pardon me, Master?
-Leave me in peace.

1749
01:13:54,543 --> 01:13:57,068
But, sir, the castle
is under attack.

1750
01:13:57,113 --> 01:13:58,341
( shouting )

1751
01:13:58,380 --> 01:14:00,211
Kill the Beast!
Kill the Beast!

1752
01:14:00,249 --> 01:14:02,012
This isn't working.

1753
01:14:02,084 --> 01:14:04,552
Oh, Lumiere,
we must do something.

1754
01:14:04,587 --> 01:14:07,021
Wait, l know.

1755
01:14:07,089 --> 01:14:09,353
( shouting )

1756
01:14:09,391 --> 01:14:12,224
What shall
we do, Master?

1757
01:14:12,261 --> 01:14:14,786
lt doesn't matter now.

1758
01:14:14,864 --> 01:14:16,889
Just let them come.

1759
01:14:16,966 --> 01:14:20,265
Kill the Beast!
Kill the Beast!

1760
01:14:20,302 --> 01:14:21,496
Kill the Beast!

1761
01:14:21,537 --> 01:14:23,004
( complete silence )

1762
01:14:28,077 --> 01:14:30,045
( murmuring )

1763
01:14:30,112 --> 01:14:31,340
( soft footsteps )

1764
01:14:34,483 --> 01:14:35,142
Now!

1765
01:14:35,184 --> 01:14:36,845
( yelling )

1766
01:14:41,857 --> 01:14:42,881
( clanking )

1767
01:14:45,394 --> 01:14:46,656
( slurping )

1768
01:14:46,695 --> 01:14:47,889
( burps )

1769
01:14:47,963 --> 01:14:51,797
( clamoring )

1770
01:14:51,834 --> 01:14:54,803
( motor chugging )

1771
01:14:54,837 --> 01:14:56,202
( blowing )

1772
01:14:56,238 --> 01:14:57,500
Yes!

1773
01:15:00,109 --> 01:15:01,007
( whistle blowing )

1774
01:15:01,110 --> 01:15:02,771
Here we go.

1775
01:15:04,446 --> 01:15:06,004
( whistle tooting )

1776
01:15:06,115 --> 01:15:07,707
What the devil?

1777
01:15:08,851 --> 01:15:10,079
Belle, look out!

1778
01:15:16,325 --> 01:15:19,453
You guys got to try this thing.

1779
01:15:19,495 --> 01:15:21,258
( screaming )

1780
01:15:24,066 --> 01:15:25,829
Up here

1781
01:15:25,901 --> 01:15:28,199
you scurvy scum! Now!

1782
01:15:28,237 --> 01:15:29,864
( man yelling )

1783
01:15:32,041 --> 01:15:34,032
( singing operatic note )

1784
01:15:46,589 --> 01:15:47,886
Oh!

1785
01:15:47,957 --> 01:15:50,926
( screaming )

1786
01:15:52,261 --> 01:15:54,286
( laughing maniacally )

1787
01:15:54,330 --> 01:15:56,730
( laughing )

1788
01:15:56,765 --> 01:15:58,892
( shuddering )

1789
01:15:58,968 --> 01:16:01,198
( yelling )

1790
01:16:03,706 --> 01:16:06,197
( screaming )

1791
01:16:09,178 --> 01:16:10,839
( crazed laughter )

1792
01:16:13,749 --> 01:16:15,649
( screaming )

1793
01:16:17,620 --> 01:16:19,588
( barking )

1794
01:16:19,622 --> 01:16:22,318
( whimpering )

1795
01:16:24,059 --> 01:16:26,027
( growling )

1796
01:16:26,128 --> 01:16:28,153
( laughing maniacally )

1797
01:16:29,365 --> 01:16:30,457
( evil laughter )

1798
01:16:30,499 --> 01:16:31,966
( screaming )

1799
01:16:34,970 --> 01:16:38,201
( cheering )

1800
01:16:38,240 --> 01:16:40,708
And stay out!

1801
01:16:42,578 --> 01:16:44,205
Eww!

1802
01:16:54,323 --> 01:16:57,349
( groans )

1803
01:16:58,394 --> 01:17:01,329
( roaring )

1804
01:17:02,731 --> 01:17:04,722
( laughing maniacally )

1805
01:17:10,172 --> 01:17:11,400
Get up.

1806
01:17:11,440 --> 01:17:12,771
( moaning )

1807
01:17:12,808 --> 01:17:15,470
Get up!

1808
01:17:15,511 --> 01:17:17,536
What's the matter, Beast?

1809
01:17:17,579 --> 01:17:18,944
( laughing )

1810
01:17:18,981 --> 01:17:21,882
Too kind and gentle
to fight back?

1811
01:17:21,951 --> 01:17:24,112
( groans )

1812
01:17:28,524 --> 01:17:29,957
BELLE:
No!

1813
01:17:31,994 --> 01:17:33,518
( horse whinnies )

1814
01:17:33,562 --> 01:17:34,290
Belle...

1815
01:17:34,330 --> 01:17:36,764
No! Gaston, don't!

1816
01:17:39,001 --> 01:17:41,231
( growling )

1817
01:17:41,270 --> 01:17:42,498
( snarling )

1818
01:17:42,538 --> 01:17:43,903
Let's go, Philippe.

1819
01:17:43,973 --> 01:17:45,440
( whinnying )

1820
01:17:50,446 --> 01:17:51,777
( groans )

1821
01:17:58,320 --> 01:18:00,811
( growling )

1822
01:18:09,031 --> 01:18:10,658
Come on out and fight!

1823
01:18:13,268 --> 01:18:16,203
Were you in love with her,
Beast?

1824
01:18:16,238 --> 01:18:19,002
Did you honestly think
she'd want you

1825
01:18:19,108 --> 01:18:21,440
when she had someone like me?

1826
01:18:24,380 --> 01:18:26,405
( growling )

1827
01:18:32,321 --> 01:18:34,983
lt's over, Beast.

1828
01:18:35,057 --> 01:18:36,752
Belle is mine!

1829
01:18:42,197 --> 01:18:43,824
Let me go. Let me go.

1830
01:18:43,866 --> 01:18:45,595
Please, don't hurt me.

1831
01:18:45,634 --> 01:18:46,658
l'll do anything.

1832
01:18:46,702 --> 01:18:48,329
Anything!

1833
01:18:58,947 --> 01:19:01,677
( Gaston moaning )

1834
01:19:01,717 --> 01:19:04,447
Get out.

1835
01:19:04,486 --> 01:19:06,681
Beast!

1836
01:19:06,722 --> 01:19:07,882
Belle?

1837
01:19:15,798 --> 01:19:17,993
Belle?

1838
01:19:23,739 --> 01:19:26,105
You came back.

1839
01:19:28,110 --> 01:19:29,077
( thud )

1840
01:19:29,178 --> 01:19:31,305
( roaring )

1841
01:19:37,820 --> 01:19:42,052
( screaming )

1842
01:19:42,124 --> 01:19:43,819
( scream stops )

1843
01:19:46,361 --> 01:19:50,957
( panting )

1844
01:20:04,279 --> 01:20:07,214
You...

1845
01:20:07,282 --> 01:20:08,909
You came back.

1846
01:20:08,951 --> 01:20:10,612
Of course l came back.

1847
01:20:10,652 --> 01:20:12,415
l couldn't let them...

1848
01:20:12,454 --> 01:20:14,388
Oh, this is all my fault.

1849
01:20:14,423 --> 01:20:16,823
lf only l'd gotten
here sooner.

1850
01:20:16,859 --> 01:20:20,351
Maybe... it's better...

1851
01:20:20,395 --> 01:20:21,692
it's better this way.

1852
01:20:21,730 --> 01:20:24,062
Don't talk like that.

1853
01:20:24,133 --> 01:20:25,725
You'll be all right.

1854
01:20:25,767 --> 01:20:26,893
( coughing )

1855
01:20:26,935 --> 01:20:27,924
We're together now.

1856
01:20:27,970 --> 01:20:29,437
Everything's
going to be fine.

1857
01:20:29,471 --> 01:20:31,666
You'll see.

1858
01:20:31,707 --> 01:20:34,972
And... at least...

1859
01:20:35,010 --> 01:20:37,740
l got to see you...

1860
01:20:37,779 --> 01:20:39,474
one last time.

1861
01:20:44,486 --> 01:20:46,477
( exhales )

1862
01:20:50,259 --> 01:20:51,851
No. No.

1863
01:20:51,894 --> 01:20:55,853
Please... Please...

1864
01:20:55,898 --> 01:20:57,832
Please, don't leave me.

1865
01:20:57,866 --> 01:21:00,027
( sobbing )

1866
01:21:00,068 --> 01:21:03,936
l love you.

1867
01:21:18,787 --> 01:21:21,779
( sobbing )

1868
01:21:39,908 --> 01:21:43,901
* *

1869
01:21:58,527 --> 01:21:59,687
* *

1870
01:22:15,844 --> 01:22:17,106
* *

1871
01:22:31,493 --> 01:22:35,520
* *

1872
01:22:41,403 --> 01:22:42,836
Belle.

1873
01:22:42,871 --> 01:22:44,532
lt's me.

1874
01:22:59,821 --> 01:23:01,516
lt is you.

1875
01:23:20,776 --> 01:23:23,870
* *

1876
01:23:34,156 --> 01:23:36,522
Lumiere.

1877
01:23:36,558 --> 01:23:39,186
Cogsworth!

1878
01:23:39,227 --> 01:23:41,422
Mrs. Potts!

1879
01:23:41,463 --> 01:23:42,623
Look at us.

1880
01:23:42,664 --> 01:23:44,188
Mama, Mama.

1881
01:23:44,232 --> 01:23:45,597
( barking )

1882
01:23:48,270 --> 01:23:49,635
( chuckling )

1883
01:23:49,671 --> 01:23:51,002
My goodness.

1884
01:23:51,039 --> 01:23:52,904
lt is a miracle.

1885
01:23:52,941 --> 01:23:55,705
( Belle laughing )

1886
01:24:02,751 --> 01:24:03,683
( sighs )

1887
01:24:03,719 --> 01:24:05,084
L'amour.

1888
01:24:07,622 --> 01:24:08,919
( lusty laugh )

1889
01:24:08,957 --> 01:24:11,255
Well, Lumiere,
old friend.

1890
01:24:11,293 --> 01:24:12,590
Shall we let bygones
be bygones?

1891
01:24:12,627 --> 01:24:13,594
Of course, mon ami.

1892
01:24:13,628 --> 01:24:15,255
l told you she would
